│ THOUGHT: The crash occurs because GVNSink creates PHI nodes for operands that are InlineAsm values. InlineAsm is a pointer-type value representing the inline assembly "function", and placing it in a PHI constitutes taking its address, which  │
│ is invalid. In sinkLastInstruction, when operands differ across predecessors, the pass creates PHIs unconditionally. We need to guard against this by skipping sinking if any operand that would require a PHI is an InlineAsm in any of the      │
│ predecessor instructions. I'll insert an early-return check in sinkLastInstruction before creating PHIs: if any differing operand is InlineAsm, bail out of sinking for this instruction.                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ applypatch << 'PATCH'                                                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ *** Begin Patch                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ *** Update File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/GVNSink.cpp                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ @@                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│    SmallVector<Value *, 4> NewOperands;                                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│    for (unsigned O = 0, E = I0->getNumOperands(); O != E; ++O) {                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│      bool NeedPHI = llvm::any_of(Insts, [&I0, O](const Instruction *I) {                                                                                                                                                                          │
│        return I->getOperand(O) != I0->getOperand(O);                                                                                                                                                                                              │
│      });                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│      if (!NeedPHI) {                                                                                                                                                                                                                              │
│        NewOperands.push_back(I0->getOperand(O));                                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│        continue;                                                                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│      }                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ +    // If creating a PHI would require putting an InlineAsm value into it,                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ +    // that would effectively take the address of inline asm, which is invalid.                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ +    // In such a case, bail out of sinking for this instruction.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ +    // This can happen when the operand is the callee of a call to inline asm,                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ +    // which is represented as a pointer-typed InlineAsm value.                                                                                                                                                                                  │
